snippet.textDisplay: Pakistani Coke studio has been all over India. As an Indian I feel this song has been written for all the freedom fighters who fought so that there could be a free India and a free Pakistan that we enjoy today. keeping aside all the hate between us it is more about unity.The one thing among so many things we have in common that both our nations sacrificed so much for our freedom. I am sure to all those Indians who are scholars of Urdu in India or even those who just appreciate just the music would have a tear rolling down their eye just like the Pakistanis would after listening to this song as a  remembrance for  "those who sacrificed their todays for our tomorrows."

snippet.textDisplay: I think everyone in this country should get an opportunity to become a legitimate singer! Mehwish Hayat?? Ayesha Omar?? Bushra Ansari?? I can't understand why people can't do their own respective jobs?? This generation has lowered the musical standards to an extent that every now and then there comes a celebrity who thinks he or she is some singing sensation! We ourselves have brought upon our destruction, no one's there to blame! There is a massive lot of immense talent striving to get a chance. Being a celebrity doesn't gives you any right to snatch away their chance to show their skills at a higher platform!
